    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462A. 62B 31/9–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Office of the United States High Commissioner for
                            Germany</gloss>, at Frankfurt</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d285fn1">This telegram, drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RJT1">Rogers</persName> and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_LGW1">Lewis</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CJA1"
                            >Calhoun</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RRH1">Riley</persName>,
                        was repeated to Bonn, Berlin, Paris, London, and Moscow.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-20T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1951—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1932. Reurtel <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 2532, rptd info Bonn 140,
                    Berlin 145, Paris 178, Moscow 24, London 192.<note n="2" xml:id="d285fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>A. Dept seriously concerned course of action outlined <gloss target="#t_reftel1"
                        >reftel</gloss>: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>It is not at all certain as yet conditions attached to sig are
                            acceptable to East. Mere absence objections on part of <persName
                                corresp="#p_OJ1">Orlopp</persName> at time signing wld not, in
                            Dept’s view, clearly signify his acceptance of conditions.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>In event it later becomes nec to suspend agmt, Western position wld
                            appear weak in absence written statement to East Gers of conditions
                                <gloss target="#t_FedRep1">FedRep</gloss> attaches to signature and
                            to continued implementation of agmt.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>B. Consequently, Dept feels strongly, agmt shld not be signed unless <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_OJ1">Orlopp</persName>’s acceptance of conditions
                            attached by West to sig agmt is clear (whether written or oral);</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_FedRep1">FedRep</gloss> statement to <persName
                                corresp="#p_OJ1">Orlopp</persName> at time of sig be made in
                            writing.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>C. Suggest this be discussed with <persName corresp="#p_MJJ1">McCloy</persName>,
                    who was present at <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>s discussion this
                    subj.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
